quest, see Customizing the Isolate Server Change Request (see  Customizing the Isolate Server Change Request ). There are two different ways to access the AlgoSec App: from the IP ...",t:"Isolating a Server"},"383":{i:0.00130868895106498,u:"../Content/afa-admin/Customizing-the-AlgoSec-App.htm",a:"The AlgoSec App supports the following customizations. Customizing the Fields Supporting AlgoSec Workflow Actions To customize the fields supporting AlgoSec workflow actions Go to Settings -\u003e Fields and choose Workflow actions. Click one of the AlgoSec actions (ABFAppLookup, ...",t:"Customizing the AlgoSec App"},"384":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/afa-admin/Using-AlgoSec-Capabilities.htm",a:"AlgoSec capabilities can be activated from within other Splunk Apps (built-in or custom) by using the Workflow Actions. By default, these actions will appear in the Action menus of IP addresses in the following field names:  source_ip dest_ip ip src_ip dst_ip source destination server_ip The IP ...",t:"Using AlgoSec Capabilities in Other Splunk Apps"},"385":{i:0.000609584398575465,u:"../Content/afa-admin/Integrating-ASMS-with-IBM.htm",a:"Integrating ASMS with IBM QRadar Supported Versions The AlgoSec IBM QRadar App v1.0.1 was tested with IBM QRadar v7.2.8 and AlgoSec Security Management Suite v6.9, v6.10 and v6.11. ",t:"Integrating ASMS with IBM QRadar"},"386":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/afa-admin/Installing-the-AlgoSec-App_1.htm",a:"To Install the AlgoSec App Download the App from IBM Security App Exchange.  Install the App using the Extensions Management tool in the Admin area. Configure the AlgoSec App, by doing the following: Go to the Admin tab. Under the Plug-ins section, find AlgoSec Security Incident Response, and click ...",t:"Installing the AlgoSec App"},"387":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/afa-admin/Viewing-Business-Impact-and_1.htm",a:"The AlgoSec App provides the ability to retrieve business application information and internet exposure information for a specific server. The information includes: Business Application context from AlgoSec BusinessFlow: names of affected applications, indication as to whether the application is ...",t:"Viewing Business Impact and Internet Exposure Information"},"388":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/afa-admin/Isolating-a-Server_1.htm",a:"You can open a FireFlow change request to isolate a risky server. There are two different ways to access the AlgoSec App: from the IP address or directly for the App. Accessing the App from the IP address will pre-populate the server field. To isolate the server from the IP address Search the logs ...",t:"Isolating a Server"},"389":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/afa-admin/Customizing-Default-Field.htm",a:"You can optionally customize the default value for any of the input fields or customize the logic of a functionality of the AlgoSec App using the IBM QRadar SDK. The App\u0027s functionalities and each of their input fields are listed below. Business Impact: Server IP Exposure to the Internet: Source IP ...",t:"Customizing Default Field Values and Logic"},"390":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/Introduction.htm",a:"AlgoSec Security Management Suite offers access to many features via web services, which are APIs that can be accessed and executed over the network. Web service APIs enable you to perform remote operations in ASMS without using the product interface directly. Web service APIs are supported via ...",t:"Introduction"},"391":{i:0.00059077632319903,u:"../Content/api-guide/AFA-REST-Web-Services.htm",a:"AFA offers a REST API which allows you to integrate AFA functionality into external applications. To view vulnerability data in AFA device reports, you must either have vulnerability scanners configured in BusinessFlow, or import your vulnerability data manually.  For more details, see  Manage ...",t:"AFA REST Web Services"},"392":{i:0.000501436911471055,u:"../Content/api-guide/Requests.htm",a:"The base URL for most REST requests is the following: https://\u003calgosec_server\u003e/fa/server where \u003calgosec_server\u003e is the AFA/FireFlow server URL. For  Retrieving Risk Profiles List  and  Retrieving Security Zones  requests, the base URL is https:://\u003calgosec_servers\u003e/afa/external. For a list of ...",t:"Requests"},"393":{i:0.000525115990003355,u:"../Content/api-guide/Logging-In.htm",a:"The AFA REST API uses sessions to avoid re-authenticating with every request. You obtain a session ID with the login request, which is used in all other REST API requests. Resource Name: /fa/server/connection/login Request Method: POST Request: Response: Request Example curl -H \"Accept: ...",t:"Logging In"},"394":{i:0.000525115990003355,u:"../Content/api-guide/Logging-Out.htm",a:"The logout request terminates the session, invalidating the session ID for any additional requests. Resource Name: /fa/server/connection/logout Request Method: POST Request: Response:  Request Example curl -k --data \"session=061e25b659d75ac22255133feb628cc2\" ...",t:"Logging Out"},"395":{i:0.000887687211912939,u:"../Content/api-guide/getting_risk_profiles_list.htm",a:"Use the sessionID to retrieve a list of risk profile Excel files for the session user. Pass the name of an Excel file in  get_zones  to retrieve the list of the security zones in each risk profile. If you have the name of the risk profile Excel file, it is not necessary to execute this API. Resource ...",t:"Retrieving Risk Profiles List"},"396":{i:0.00127965478485758,u:"../Content/api-guide/getting_security_zones.htm",a:"The get_zones method retrieves a list of the Security Zone names and IP ranges for each zone listed in the Networks tab of the passed risk profile Excel spreadsheet. If the spreadsheet name is known, it is not necessary to call  get_profiles_list. Related screens in ASMS are the Security Zones ...",t:"Retrieving Security Zones"},"397":{i:0.000525115990003355,u:"../Content/api-guide/Retrieving-Network-Objects.htm",a:"The get_network_objects request retrieves all the network objects of a device or a group of devices, along with the IP addresses contained in each object.  The input will be the active session ID and the name of a device or a device group. The output will be a list of all the network objects of all ...",t:"Retrieving Network Objects"},"398":{i:0.000525115990003355,u:"../Content/api-guide/Retrieving-Service-Objects.htm",a:"The get_service_objects request retrieves all the service objects of a device or a group of devices, along with the protocol and ports contained in each object. The input will be the active session ID and the name of a device or a device group. The output will be a list of all the service objects of ...",t:"Retrieving Service Objects"},"399":{i:0.000501436911471055,u:"../Content/api-guide/afa-import-risks-xml.htm",a:"Import risks from XML The import_risks_from_xml request imports risks to a custom risk profile from an XML file. Request Method: PUT Request URL Parameters: Response:",t:"Import risks from XML"},"400":{i:0.000501436911471055,u:"../Content/api-guide/afa-import-risks-spreadsheet.htm",a:"Import risks from spreadsheet The import_risks_from_spreadsheet request imports risks to a custom risk profile from a spreadsheet file. Request Method: PUT Request URL Parameters: Response:",t:"Import risks from spreadsheet"},"401":{i:0.000501436911471055,u:"../Content/api-guide/afa-ret-containing-obj.htm",a:"Retrieve containing objects The get_containing_objects request retrieves a list of containing objects for a specified object. Request Method: GET Request URL Parameters: Response:",t:"Retrieve containing objects"},"402":{i:0.000501436911471055,u:"../Content/api-guide/afa-ret-license.htm",a:"Retrieve license The get_license request retrieves details about the current ASMS license installed. Request Method: GET Response:",t:"Retrieve license"},"403":{i:0.000501436911471055,u:"../Content/api-guide/afa-ret-parent-obj.htm",a:"Retrieve parent object The get_parent_device request retrieves the parent object of a specified device. Request Method: GET Request URL Parameters: Response:",t:"Retrieve parent object"},"404":{i:0.000501436911471055,u:"../Content/api-guide/afa-search-by-ip.htm",a:"Search for object by IP The search_object_by_ip request performs a search in AFA for all objects that match the details provided in the request. Request Method: GET Request URL Parameters: Response:",t:"Search for object by IP"},"405":{i:0.000525115990003355,u:"../Content/api-guide/Retrieving-Rules.htm",a:"The get_rules request retrieves all the rules in a device\u0027s or group\u0027s policy. The input will be the active session ID and the name of the device, group, or matrix. The output will be a list of all the rules of all the policies that apply to each device, including the value of each rule field. ...",t:"Retrieving Rules"},"406":{i:0.000525115990003355,u:"../Content/api-guide/Retrieving-Risky-Rules.htm",a:"The riskyRules_get request retrieves all the risky rules in a device\u0027s or group\u0027s policy. The input will be the active session ID and the name of the device, group, or matrix. The output will be a list of all risky rules of all the policies that apply to each device, including the risk severity of ...",t:"Retrieving Risky Rules"},"407":{i:0.000525115990003355,u:"../Content/api-guide/Retrieving-Interfaces.htm",a:"The get_interfaces request retrieves the interfaces of a device or a group/matrix of devices, along with their IP addresses.  The input will be the active session ID and the name of a device, group, or matrix. The output will be a list of all the interfaces of all the devices in the selected group ...",t:"Retrieving Interfaces"},"408":{i:0.000501436911471055,u:"../Content/api-guide/retrieving_users.htm",a:"The get_users request retrieves AFA users data.  The input will be the active session ID and a domain ID (optional) for multi-domain environments. The output will be only the users of the input domain (if there is a domain ID). Resource Name: /afa/external/users/getUsers Request Method: GET Request ...",t:"Retrieve user data"},"409":{i:0.000501436911471055,u:"../Content/api-guide/retrieving_roles.htm",a:"The get_roles request retrieves AFA roles data.  The input will be the active session ID and a domain ID (optional) for multi-domain environments. The output will be only the roles of the input domain (if there is a domain ID). Resource Name: /afa/external/users/getRoles Request Method: GET ...",t:"Retrieving Roles Data"},"410":{i:0.000525115990003355,u:"../Content/api-guide/Starting-an-Analysis.htm",a:"The start_analysis request initiates an analysis on a device, group, or matrix.  The input will be the active session ID and the name of the device, group, or matrix. The output will include a status and message which indicates success or failure. Resource Name: /fa/server/analysis/start Request ...",t:"Starting an Analysis"},"411":{i:0.000525115990003355,u:"../Content/api-guide/Retrieving-an-Analysis-Status.htm",a:"The get_analysis_status request retrieves the current status of an analysis.  The input will be the active session ID and the device, group or matrix. The output will indicate the status of the analysis. Resource Name: /fa/server/analysis/status Request Method: GET Request URL Parameters: Response: ...",t:"Retrieving an Analysis Status"},"412":{i:0.000525115990003355,u:"../Content/api-guide/retrieving_a_base_compliance_report.htm",a:"The baseline_compliance request retrieves the baseline compliance report for a device.  The input will be the active session ID and the device name. The output will be the Baseline Compliance Report in JSON format. Resource Name: /afa/external/baseline_compliance Request Method: GET Request URL ...",t:"Retrieving a Baseline Compliance Report"},"413":{i:0.000525115990003355,u:"../Content/api-guide/Assigning-Zone-Types-to-Interfaces.htm",a:"The update_interfaces request assigns a zone type to each of a device\u0027s interfaces. The input will be the active session ID, the name of the device, and the zone type for each interface. The output will include a status and message which indicates success or failure. Note: This request requires ...",t:"Assigning Zone Types to Interfaces"},"414":{i:0.000525115990003355,u:"../Content/api-guide/Identifying-Missing-Routers.htm",a:"The following requests allow you to identify routers in the AFA graphic network map that should be defined as devices in AFA. For more information about this tool, see the AlgoSec Firewall Analyzer Administrator Guide, Completing the Map. Executing the Map Completeness Tool (see  Executing the Map ...",t:"Identifying Missing Routers"},"415":{i:0.00057396831622034,u:"../Content/api-guide/Executing-the-Map-Completeness.htm",a:"The execute method runs the map completeness tool. This tool searches for routers missing from the AFA graphic network map. The input will be the network\u0027s SNMP key, internal networks, external networks, and the maximum number of queries the tool should run. The output is a status message. To ...",t:"Executing the Map Completeness Tool"},"416":{i:0.000817906054681474,u:"../Content/api-guide/Retrieving-Missing-Routers.htm",a:"The missingStubRouters request provides the results of the execute request: a list of routers missing from the graphic network map. The input will be the page number you want to retrieve. You can optionally filter the result that you want to retrieve by providing the name of a router, the name of ...",t:"Retrieving Missing Routers Results"},"417":{i:0.00057396831622034,u:"../Content/api-guide/Retrieving-the-Configuration.htm",a:"The lastExecution request provides the parameters that were used the last time the map completeness tool was executed. Resource Name: ms-mapDiagnostics/v1/api/mapCompleteness/lastExecution*/ Request Method: GET Authentication: Cookie with session ID. Response: Response Example { \"score\": 43, ...",t:"Retrieving the Configuration of the Last Execution"},"418":{i:0.00057396831622034,u:"../Content/api-guide/Aborting-a-Map-Completeness.htm",a:"Aborting a Map Completeness Job The abort request stops an execution that is in progress. Resource Name: ms-mapDiagnostics/v1/api/mapCompleteness/abort*/ Request Method: POST Authentication: Cookie with session ID. Response:",t:"Aborting a Map Completeness Job"},"419":{i:0.000817906054681474,u:"../Content/api-guide/Retrieving-Map-Completeness.htm",a:"The defaultValues request provides the default values of the map completeness tool parameters for the specific AFA environment.  By default, the maximum number of paths that will be simulated (queries that will be run) is 400. The default external networks used in the calculation is 8.8.8.8. If a ...",t:"Retrieving Map Completeness Default Values"},"420":{i:0.000525115990003355,u:"../Content/api-guide/Merging-Routers.htm",a:"Following are the Public AFA APIs available for Merged Routers Management: POST - Merge routers (see  Merging Routers ) GET - Retrieve a list of merged routers (see  Retrieving a List of Merged Routers ) GET - Retrieve the status of merged router process (see  Retrieving Status of Merged Routers )  ...",t:"Merging Routers"},"421":{i:0.000596285853730916,u:"../Content/api-guide/Retrieving-a-List-of-Merged.htm",a:"Retrieves a list of merged routers with the status \"MERGED\" only. Merged routers with the status \"OUTDATED_MERGED\" are excluded. Resource URL: /mergeRouters/list Resource Method: GET Authentication: Cookie with session ID. Response: Response Example: [    {       \"id\":35,       \"name\":\"router1\", ...",t:"Retrieving a List of Merged Routers"},"422":{i:0.000596285853730916,u:"../Content/api-guide/Retrieving-Status-of-Merged.htm",a:"Retrieving Status of Merged Routers Retrieve the status of the current or the last running process of merged stubs. This request is usually used for an asynchronous process. Resource URL: /mergeRouters/status Resource Method: GET Authentication: Cookie with session ID. Response:",t:"Retrieving Status of Merged Routers"},"423":{i:0.000596285853730916,u:"../Content/api-guide/Merging-Routers_1.htm",a:"Merges routers: Stub routers into a merged router. Merges merged routers into another merged router. Adds stub routers and/or merged routers into a merged router. Routers that are merged with the API are stored in the DB table \u0027merge_router_job\u0027 and can only be unmerged using the /unmerge API. ...",t:"Merging Routers"},"424":{i:0.000596285853730916,u:"../Content/api-guide/Unmerging-Routers.htm",a:"Unmerges a merged router. Only routers merged by the API and stored in the merged_router_job table can be unmerged with the API. Resource URL: /mergeRouters/unmerge Resource Method: POST Authentication: Cookie with session ID. Request Body: Response: Request Example: { \"name:\"router1\" }",t:"Unmerging Routers"},"425":{i:0.000525115990003355,u:"../Content/api-guide/Running-the-Query-Troubleshooting.htm",a:"The troubleshoot method helps to determine why a group traffic simulation query produced an inaccurate traffic path. The input is the ID of the query ran in the online wizard and a list of the expected devices on the query path. The output is a response message with the found paths, detected ...",t:"Running the Query Troubleshooting Tool"},"426":{i:0.000525115990003355,u:"../Content/api-guide/Managing-Issues.htm",a:"Managing Issues Use the following request methods to manage issues in the AFA issues center. All of the API requests for managing issues can only be run by administrators. In a distributed architecture environment, they can only be run on the central manager / master appliance.",t:"Managing Issues"},"427":{i:0.00130868895106498,u:"../Content/api-guide/Retrieving-Unresolved-Issues.htm",a:"The get_issues request retrieves all the unresolved issues in the AFA issues center. This includes both acknowledged and active issues.  Resource Name:/ms-watchdog/v1/api/issues-center/issues Request Method: POST Authentication: Cookie with session ID. Request URL Parameters:  Request Body:  ...",t:"Retrieving Unresolved Issues"},"428":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/Acknowledging-an-Issue.htm",a:"The acknowledge request marks active issues in the AFA issues center as acknowledged. Issues marked as acknowledged will appear in the list of acknowledged issues and will no longer appear in the list of active issues.  Resource Name:/ms-watchdog/v1/api/issues-center/issues/acknowledge Request ...",t:"Acknowledging an Issue"},"429":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/Activating-an-Issue.htm",a:"The activate request marks acknowledged issues in the AFA issues center as active. Issues marked as active will appear in the list of active issues and will no longer appear in the list of acknowledged issues.  Resource Name:/ms-watchdog/v1/api/issues-center/issues/activate Request Method: POST ...",t:"Activating an Issue"},"430":{i:0.0013941384118941,u:"../Content/api-guide/Data-Types_1.htm",a:"Data Types EntitiesResponse Type",t:"Data Types"},"431":{i:0.00114724197193228,u:"../Content/api-guide/action_type.htm",a:"Action Type",t:"Action Type"},"432":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/addobjectstoGroup_type.htm",a:"AddObjectsToGroup Type",t:"AddObjectsToGroup Type"},"433":{i:0.000931048916389558,u:"../Content/api-guide/BaselineRequirementsResult_Type.htm",a:"BaselineRequirementResult Type",t:"BaselineRequirementResult Type"},"434":{i:0.00127609398101549,u:"../Content/api-guide/BaselineRequirementTestResult_Type.htm",a:"BaselineRequirementTestResult Type  ",t:"BaselineRequirementTestResult Type"},"435":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/create_type.htm",a:"Create Type",t:"Create Type"},"436":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/delete_type.htm",a:"Delete Type",t:"Delete Type"},"437":{i:0.000559089957879956,u:"../Content/api-guide/ExpectedDevice-Type.htm",a:"ExpectedDevice Type",t:"ExpectedDevice Type"},"438":{i:0.000559089957879956,u:"../Content/api-guide/ExpectedQueryDevice-Type.htm",a:"ExpectedQueryDevice Type",t:"ExpectedQueryDevice Type"},"439":{i:0.00277095371084505,u:"../Content/api-guide/fields_type.htm",a:"Fields Type",t:"Fields Type"},"440":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/FirstUnexpectedDevice-Type.htm",a:"FirstUnexpectedDevice Type",t:"FirstUnexpectedDevice Type"},"441":{i:0.00159708985579146,u:"../Content/api-guide/Issue-Type.htm",a:"IssueAttributes Type",t:"IssueAttributes Type"},"442":{i:0.000991543664220003,u:"../Content/api-guide/MergedRoutersData-Type.htm",a:"MergedRoutersData Type",t:"MergedRoutersData Type"},"443":{i:0.000653646665525358,u:"../Content/api-guide/MergedRoutersToMerge-Type.htm",a:"MergedRoutersToMerge Type",t:"MergedRoutersToMerge Type"},"444":{i:0.00232482215278064,u:"../Content/api-guide/messagedetails_type.htm",a:"MessageDetails Type",t:"MessageDetails Type"},"445":{i:0.000653646665525358,u:"../Content/api-guide/MixedMergedRouters-Type.htm",a:"MixedMergedRouters Type",t:"MixedMergedRouters Type"},"446":{i:0.000622029963659193,u:"../Content/api-guide/natdetails_type.htm",a:"NatDetails Type",t:"NatDetails Type"},"447":{i:0.000931048916389558,u:"../Content/api-guide/Interface-Type.htm",a:"Interface Type",t:"Interface Type"},"448":{i:0.0018027436978678,u:"../Content/api-guide/Network-Type.htm",a:"Network Type",t:"Network Type"},"449":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/objectchangerequestdetails_type1.htm",a:"ObjectChangeRequestDetails Type",t:"ObjectChangeRequestDetails Type"},"450":{i:0.000559089957879956,u:"../Content/api-guide/QueryNetworkObject-Type.htm",a:"QueryNetworkObject Type",t:"QueryNetworkObject Type"},"451":{i:0.000559089957879956,u:"../Content/api-guide/QueryTroubleshootingInconsistencyCause.htm",a:"QueryTroubleshootingInconsistencyCause Type",t:"QueryTroubleshootingInconsistencyCause Type"},"452":{i:0.000559089957879956,u:"../Content/api-guide/QueryTroubleshootingPathItem.htm",a:"QueryTroubleshootingPathItem Type",t:"QueryTroubleshootingPathItem Type"},"453":{i:0.000559089957879956,u:"../Content/api-guide/QueryTroubleshootingScenario.htm",a:"QueryTroubleshootingScenario Type",t:"QueryTroubleshootingScenario Type"},"454":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/removeobjectsfromgroup_type.htm",a:"RemoveObjectsFromGroup Type",t:"RemoveObjectsFromGroup Type"},"455":{i:0.000931048916389558,u:"../Content/api-guide/RiskyRules.htm",a:"RiskyRules JSON Format CSV Format",t:"RiskyRules"},"456":{i:0.001179921995187,u:"../Content/api-guide/Stub-Type.htm",a:"Stub Type",t:"Stub Type"},"457":{i:0.000847269388087619,u:"../Content/api-guide/securityzoneobject_type.htm",a:"SecurityZoneObject Type",t:"SecurityZoneObject Type"},"458":{i:0.000653646665525358,u:"../Content/api-guide/StubsToMerge-Type.htm",a:"StubsToMerge Type",t:"StubsToMerge Type"},"459":{i:0.000735246579488807,u:"../Content/api-guide/trafficchangerequest_type.htm",a:"TrafficChangeRequest Type  ",t:"TrafficChangeRequest Type"},"460":{i:0.000622029963659193,u:"../Content/api-guide/trafficfielddetails_type.htm",a:"TrafficFieldDetails Type",t:"TrafficFieldDetails Type"},"461":{i:0.0010134262748165,u:"../Content/api-guide/trafficitemdetails_type.htm",a:"TrafficItemDetails Type",t:"TrafficItemDetails Type"},"462":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/api-guide/trafficlinedetails_type.htm",a:"TrafficLineDetails Type",t:"TrafficLineDetails Type"},"463":{i:0.00166972242454739,u:"../Content/api-guide/Value-Type.htm",a:"Value Type There is a value object type for network objects, and a value object type for service objects. Value Type for Network Objects   Value Type for Service Objects",t:"Value Type"},"464":{i:0.000501436911471055,u:"../Content/api-guide/AFA-Search-Rule-Fields.htm",a:"AFA Search Rule Fields The following are lists of possible search field values based on the devices searched.  Note: If no device is selected, the search is run on all devices.",t:"AFA Search Rule Fields"},});
/usr/share/fa/php/help/Data/SearchTopic_Chunk3.js:1:define({"221":{i:0.000484698166178036,u:"../Content/afa-admin/Customizing-Risk-and-Compliance.htm",a:"AFA supports many risk and compliance customizations, allowing you to define your organization\u0027s specific needs. Note: For information on how to customize the network topology and/or specify traffic that should always be treated as non-threatening, see the AlgoSec Firewall Analyzer User Guide, ...",t:"Customizing Risk and Compliance Management"},"222":{i:0.00063426993270247,u:"../Content/afa-admin/Customizing-Risk-Profiles.htm",a:"AFAanalyzes device configuration ans reports security risks using risk profiles, which define sets of security risk items and their security levels. By default, AFA uses a Standard Risk Profile for all devices, which includes a set of standard risk items. Each risk item represents an XQL query that ...",t:"Customize risk profiles"},"223":{i:0.0022985149386845,u:"../Content/afa-admin/Viewing-Risk-Profiles.htm",a:"This procedure describes how to view a specific risk profile in the AFA Administration area, as well as the details shown. Do the following: Access the AFA Administration area. Click your username in the toolbar and select Administration. Click the Compliance \u003e Risk Profiles tab, displaying the ...",t:"View a risk profile"},"224":{i:0.00140688628365092,u:"../Content/afa-admin/Adding-Risk-Profiles.htm",a:"Add a new risk profile by creating one from scratch, modifying an existing profile and saving it under a new name, or importing a spreadsheet that specifies safe traffic. In this topic: /* */ Create a new risk profile from scratch Create a new risk profile from scratch when you want to start with ...",t:"Add a new risk profile"},"225":{i:0.0011079203390432,u:"../Content/afa-admin/Deleting-Risk-Profiles.htm",a:"Delete any unused risk profiles to declutter your system. Do the following: View the specific risk profile you want to delete in the Risk Profiles tab in the AFA A